Odd, I'm not sure why that doesn't work when the cocoa.m configuration
appears on the surface to be similar enough. (The pvg and metal
dependencies aren't available obviously, I'd have thought that should be
enough.) Oh well, wrapping the PVG lines with

if host_os =3D=3D 'darwin'
=E2=80=A6
endif

Seems to fix it and it still works on macOS. There are a few other places
in the build system doing the same thing, so I'll go with that.



